reviewText: Good subject, but DVD was loos in side of the case and was scratched up when it arrived. No external wrapping on the DVD case so could have easily  opened the case and made sure DVD was secured.

The late Jeff Ethel brings you along inside the cockpit as he preflights, flies, and lands one of the most recognizable combat aircraft in the world. Born in less than 120 days, the Mustang was originally meant for the British. The weak, at altitude, Allison engine gave way to the powerful Rolls-Royce Merlin V-12, thus transforming the North American Aviation prodigy into a warbird that made many aces and gave the Luftwaffe a mortal headache. Laminar-flow wings come to life as Ethel puts the Mustang through its paces. A thoroughbred in all respects, the P-51 retains its place in aviation as one of the best.
Great overview of the P-51 Mustang with camera views in the cockpit. This is a great DVD for anybody interested in WWII aircraft.
